    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2006-09-14</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2006-11-30T20:33:11Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Border Death Reduction Act of 2006 - Directs the Commissioner of Customs to begin collecting data relevant to deaths occurring at the U.S.-Mexico border, divided by sector, and including: (1) causes, locations, and number of deaths; and (2) demographic characteristics, including the sex and approximate age of those deceased.</p> <p>Directs the Commissioner to report to the Secretary of Homeland Security respecting: (1) annual border deaths; and (2) rescue beacon (as defined by this Act) placement.</p> <p>Directs the Commissioner to deploy additional rescue beacons in all areas recommended in such report.</p> <p>States that any person who commits an alien-smuggling related act and, in the course of such act, abandons an alien in a place not within sight of a paved road or rescue beacon shall be considered to have placed a person's life in jeopardy and subject to fine and/or up to 20 years in prison.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
